Add a full real-time RL telemetry and visualization dashboard.

The visualization should NOT only render the aircraft.

It should also visualize:
- current training objective
- current mission target
- current reward
- reward breakdown
- PPO training statistics
- convergence indicators
- flight state
- mission progress
- policy behavior

============================================================
REAL-TIME TRAINING TELEMETRY
============================================================

Display live PPO metrics:

- total timesteps
- episode number
- episode reward
- moving average reward
- best reward
- current learning rate
- policy loss
- value loss
- entropy
- approx_kl
- explained_variance
- FPS
- training iteration
- success rate
- crash rate
- landing success rate
- waypoint completion rate

Render these as:
- HUD text
- scrolling graphs
- mini dashboards
- color-coded indicators

============================================================
FLIGHT TELEMETRY HUD
============================================================

Display:

- mode
- airspeed
- altitude
- heading
- roll
- pitch
- yaw
- vertical speed
- throttle
- control surface deflections
- distance to waypoint
- glide slope error
- runway alignment error
- angle of attack approximation
- stall warning
- g-load approximation

============================================================
MISSION VISUALIZATION
============================================================

Render:
- waypoint markers
- current target
- loiter orbit
- runway
- glide slope line
- trajectory trail/history
- predicted velocity vector
- target vector
- path history

============================================================
TRAINING GOAL VISUALIZATION
============================================================

Show visually:
- what the agent is currently trying to optimize
- active reward terms
- current reward breakdown

Example:
Reward Breakdown:
+ waypoint_progress: +1.23
- excessive_bank: -0.12
- sink_rate: -0.45
+ runway_alignment: +0.88

============================================================
CONVERGENCE VISUALIZATION
============================================================

Add:
- scrolling reward graph
- moving average reward graph
- crash frequency graph
- success frequency graph
- PPO loss graphs

Use simple pygame-rendered line graphs.

============================================================
EVENT SYSTEM
============================================================

Display temporary events:
- STALL WARNING
- GOOD LANDING
- CRASH
- WAYPOINT REACHED
- MODE SWITCH
- RECOVERY ACTIVATED

============================================================
CAMERA MODES
============================================================

Keyboard:
F1 = cinematic chase camera
F2 = side view
F3 = top-down tactical view
F4 = cockpit-ish forward view

============================================================
TRAINING ARCHITECTURE
============================================================

IMPORTANT:
Renderer remains READ-ONLY.

Trainer thread:
- owns PPO
- owns env
- updates shared telemetry state

Renderer:
- visualizes shared telemetry only
- never mutates env
- never calls env.step()
- never calls model.predict()

============================================================
VISUAL STYLE
============================================================

Style:
- dark aerospace-style UI
- horizon
- artificial horizon indicator
- green HUD symbology
- modern flight-test aesthetic
- smooth 60 FPS rendering

============================================================
PERFORMANCE
============================================================

Keep renderer lightweight:
- avoid matplotlib
- use pygame primitive drawing
- use bounded telemetry history buffers

============================================================
IMPLEMENTATION ORDER
============================================================

Implement incrementally:

1. shared telemetry state
2. flight HUD
3. reward breakdown
4. training metrics
5. scrolling graphs
6. mission overlays
7. camera modes
8. event system

Prefer working visualization over overengineered abstractions.